# 7. Planned Mobile Improvements

## App System
- Grid-based app drawer (replacing vertical list)
- App tiles with icons
- Sorting and layout improvements

## UI System
- Reusable components
- Home screen panels
- Widget system (clock, shortcuts, system info)

## Input System (Future)
- Phone becomes trackpad
- Phone becomes keyboard
- Gesture controls

---

# 8. Desktop System (Future)

A custom desktop environment will be created.

It will include:

- Custom taskbar
- Window management system
- Lightweight UI shell
- App rendering system
- Widget support

It is designed to:
- Run on low-spec devices
- Avoid heavy system overhead
- Replace or overlay existing desktop UI

---

# 9. Communication System (Critical Concept)

Devices will communicate using:

- Network connection (WiFi initially)
- Event-based messages

Example messages:

- OPEN_APP: com.example.app
- MOVE_MOUSE: x,y
- CLICK: left/right
- TYPE_KEY: A

---

# 10. Theme System (Planned)

A shared theme model will control appearance across devices.

- Android uses Material You style
- Desktop uses Fluent UI style
- Shared core theme defines:
  - spacing
  - colours
  - corner rounding
  - layout density

---

# 11. Major Insight So Far

The system is not:

- A launcher
- A remote control app
- A desktop clone

It is:

A distributed interface system connecting mobile and desktop into one controllable environment.

